Today I present to you the "material of the soul".
Artwork generates three-dimensional waves, creating an incredible pattern of matter.

metadata.name: Siren #28
metadata.description:
In the book "The Art of Computer Designing", Osamu Sato illustrates how unexpected shapes emerge when a shape that is the color of the background, overlaps a shape that is a different color. I kept this in mind while experimenting with an algorithm by bobsarea that divides any circle by N. 

Siren produces each output by taking (rings, lines, and points) of either (red, black, or white) in sizes ranging from (small to large), and placing them around the perimeter of a centered circle N times in (randomized distances) from the center, on a background of (red, black, or white).

2022 (CC0 1.0)

metadata.name: Towers of Power #23
metadata.description:
In this generative art illustration, I wanted to represent the power of the upper class against as tall towers against and covering a starred sky. 
I sketched the towers with vertical and horizontal lines, circles, and ellipses to represent the power and control that they have. 
A light, transparent and, yet big, sun is sketched in the background to represent the hope that the poor and minorities have for justice and a better world.

This illustration is created within my research effort to recreate in the digital medium my style of physical acrylic painting that uses paint drips on technical drawings and textured background.

Three modes: dark, light and gold.
Many form factors.

Hit 's' to save a svg
Hit 'p' to save a png

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #8

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #8
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of “grain” appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.

issuer.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I.

metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #5241
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
